        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The God who made and sustains the life of every human being. In early days Jehovah was thought of as the particular deity of Israel alone. But by the time of the priestly writer the nation had long advanced to the deeper and truer conception of monotheism.",
